/**
 * @file meta.pxd
 * @brief Cython declaration file for the @c meta C++ class and associated
 *        Python helpers @c Meta, @c MetaLookup, @c Data, and @c ami_client.
 * @details Wraps the @c meta class that caches dataset metadata from AMI and
 *          the local ROOT file headers.
 */

/**
 * @class Meta
 * @brief Python wrapper for @c meta.
 * @details Stores ATLAS dataset metadata fetched from AMI or derived from the
 *          ROOT file headers.  Instances are created automatically by the
 *          analysis framework; you can also create them manually and set
 *          `FetchMeta = True` to trigger a live AMI lookup.
 *
 * **Methods:**
 * - `GetSumOfWeights(name: str) -> float` — Return the sum of weights for
 *   the named sub-sample; returns 1 if unavailable.
 * - `hash(val: str) -> str` — Return the hash of `val` as managed by the
 *   underlying `meta` object.
 * - `expected_events(lumi: float = 140.1) -> float` — Expected number of
 *   events: `crossSection × lumi`.
 *
 * **Properties (read/write):**
 * - `AtlasRelease` (str) — ATLAS software release.
 * - `DatasetName` (str) — Logical dataset name.
 * - `FetchMeta` (bool) — If True, trigger a live AMI lookup.
 * - `Files` (dict) — Map from sequential index to input file path.
 * - `GetSumOfWeights` — Sum-of-weights lookup.
 * - `MetaCachePath` (str) — Path to the HDF5 cache file used to persist
 *   AMI lookups.
 * - `PDF` (str) — PDF set used for generation.
 * - `SumOfWeights` — Raw misc map from the C++ `meta_t` struct.
 * - `amiStatus` (str) — AMI status string.
 * - `amitag` (str) — AMI processing tag (e.g. `"r13829_r13726_p6026"`).
 * - `beamType` (str) — Beam type (e.g. `"collisions"`).
 * - `beam_energy` (float) — Beam energy in GeV.
 * - `campaign` (str) — MC campaign tag (e.g. `"mc21a"`).
 * - `completion` (float) — Dataset processing completion fraction (0–100).
 * - `conditionsTag` (str) — Conditions database tag.
 * - `config` (dict) — Miscellaneous configuration key/value pairs.
 * - `crossSection` (float) — Cross-section (getter multiplies stored value
 *   by 10⁶ to convert from stored units to fb).
 * - `crossSection_mean` (float) — Mean cross-section in pb.
 * - `dataType` (str) — Data type string (e.g. `"DAOD_TOPQ1"`).
 * - `datasetNumber` (int) — Secondary dataset number.
 * - `derivationFormat` (str) — ATLAS derivation format (e.g. `"TOPQ1"`).
 * - `dsid` (int) — Dataset identifier (DSID).
 * - `ecmEnergy` (float) — Centre-of-mass energy in GeV.
 * - `eventNumber` (float) — Current event number.
 * - `event_index` (int) — Index of the current event.
 * - `events` (dict) — Map from LFN to number of events.
 * - `expected_events` (float) — Expected events at a given luminosity.
 * - `fileGUID` (dict) — Map from LFN to file GUID.
 * - `fileSize` (dict) — Map from LFN to file size in bytes.
 * - `file_type` (str) — File type string.
 * - `found` (bool) — True if the AMI lookup succeeded.
 * - `genFiltEff` (float) — Generator filter efficiency.
 * - `genFilterNames` (str) — Generator filter names.
 * - `generatorName` (str) — Generator name.
 * - `generatorTune` (str) — Generator tune (e.g. `"A14"`).
 * - `generators` (str) — Generator string (e.g. `"Pythia8 Herwig7"`).
 * - `geometryVersion` (str) — Geometry version tag.
 * - `hash` (str) — Hash identifier of this Meta instance.
 * - `identifier` (str) — AMI logical identifier string.
 * - `isMC` (bool) — True for Monte-Carlo samples.
 * - `keyword` (list) — Secondary keyword list.
 * - `keywords` (list) — AMI keyword list.
 * - `kfactor` (float) — K-factor applied to the cross-section.
 * - `logicalDatasetName` (str) — Full logical dataset name from AMI.
 * - `nFiles` (int) — Number of files in the dataset.
 * - `physicsShort` (str) — Short physics description.
 * - `principalPhysicsGroup` (str) — Primary physics group owning the sample.
 * - `prodsysStatus` (str) — Production system status string.
 * - `productionStep` (str) — Production step name.
 * - `projectName` (str) — Project name.
 * - `run_number` (list) — Run numbers associated with the dataset.
 * - `sample_name` (str) — Short sample name.
 * - `statsAlgorithm` (str) — Statistics algorithm used.
 * - `totalEvents` (int) — Total number of events in the dataset.
 * - `totalSize` (float) — Total dataset size in bytes.
 * - `version` (str) — Dataset version tag.
 * - `weights` (list) — Generator weight names.
 */

/**
 * @class MetaLookup
 * @brief Provides dataset lookup and luminosity weighting.
 * @details Caches matched @c Meta objects and their metadata dicts.  Used
 *          as the return type of `Analysis.GetMetaData`.
 *
 * **Constructor:**
 * - `MetaLookup(data: MetaLookup = None)` — Optionally copy the metadata
 *   dict from another `MetaLookup`.
 *
 * **Callable interface:**
 * - `__call__(inpt: str | bytes) -> MetaLookup` — Look up the `Meta` object
 *   whose hash matches `inpt`; caches the result in `matched`.
 *
 * **Read-only derived properties (valid after a successful `__call__`):**
 * - `CrossSection` (float) — Cross-section of the matched `Meta`.
 * - `DatasetName` (str) — Dataset name of the matched `Meta`.
 * - `ExpectedEvents` (float) — Expected number of events:
 *   `CrossSection × luminosity`.
 * - `GenerateData` — Return a new `Data` instance linked to this lookup for
 *   weight rescaling.
 * - `SumOfWeights` — Sum of weights (returns 1 in current implementation).
 *
 * **Attributes:**
 * - `luminosity` (float) — Integrated luminosity in fb⁻¹ (default 140.1).
 * - `matched` — The last `Meta` object matched by `__call__`.
 * - `meta` — Internal meta cache.
 * - `metadata` (dict) — All registered `Meta` objects keyed by
 *   `"<hash>-<DatasetName>"`.
 */

/**
 * @class Data
 * @brief Aggregates event data arrays and computes sum-of-weights rescaling.
 * @details Linked to a `MetaLookup`; collects per-file data and weight arrays
 *          and rescales them by `ExpectedEvents / SumOfWeights` when the
 *          `weights` property is read.
 *
 * **Properties (read/write):**
 * - `data` (vector[float], read / dict setter) — Concatenated data array;
 *   assigning a dict `{filename: values}` populates the internal data map.
 * - `weights` (vector[float], read / dict setter) — Rescaled concatenated
 *   weight vector; assigning a dict `{filename: weights}` populates the
 *   internal weight map.
 *
 * **Operator support:**
 * - `__add__(other: Data) -> Data` — Merge weight and data maps from `other`.
 * - `__radd__(other) -> Data` — Allows `sum([d1, d2, ...])`.
 */

/**
 * @class ami_client
 * @brief Python client for fetching metadata from AMI.
 * @details Wraps a `pyAMI.client.Client` with an unverified HTTPS connection
 *          context and provides cache load/save and metadata dressing for
 *          `Meta` objects.  Constructed automatically during `Meta.FetchMeta`.
 *
 *          Uses HDF5 (via h5py) to cache raw AMI responses so repeated
 *          lookups for the same DSID do not require a network round-trip.
 */

